3682\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  PDF\n</a>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n    </div>\n    \n\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"ml-3\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n</div>\n\n          \n        </div>\n\n        \n\n        \n          \n        \n\n        <div class=\"grid-sizer col-lg-12 isotope-item pubtype-1 year-2013\">\n          \n            \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n\n<div class=\"media stream-item\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ScholarlyArticle\">\n  <div class=\"media-body\">\n\n    <h3 class=\"article-title mb-0 mt-0\" itemprop=\"name\">\n      <a href=\"/~perl/publication/pg_diversity/\" itemprop=\"url\">Profile-guided Automatic Software Diversity</a>\n    </h3>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"article-style\" itemprop=\"articleBody\">\n      Code-reuse attacks are notoriously hard to defeat, and most current solutions to the problem focus on automated software diversity. \u2026\n    </div>\n    \n\n    <div class=\"stream-meta article-metadata\">\n\n      \n\n      \n        \n\n\n\n<meta content=\"2013-02-23 00:00:00 &#43;0000 UTC\" itemprop=\"datePublished\">\n<meta content=\"2013-02-23 00:00:00 &#43;0000 UTC\" itemprop=\"dateModified\">\n\n<div class=\"article-metadata\">\n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n  <div>\n    <span>Andrei Homescu</span>\n    <span>Steven Neisius</span>\n    <span>Per Larsen</span>\n    <span>Stefan Brunthaler</span>\n    <span>Michael Franz</span>\n    \n  </div>\n  \n  \n\n  \n  <span class=\"article-date\">\n    \n    \n      \n    \n    <time>February, 2013</time>\n  </span>\n  \n\n  \n  <span class=\"middot-divider\"></span>\n  <span class=\"pub-publication\">\n    \n      In <em>CGO</em>\n    \n  </span>\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n</div>\n\n      \n    </div>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"btn-links\">\n      \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n  \n\n\n<a class=\"btn btn-outline-primary my-1 mr-1 btn-sm\" href=\"https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2495928\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  PDF\n</a>\n\n\n\n\n